.TH "SQUEEZE" "1" "2026\-04\-11" "Winix" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
squeeze \- compress and decompress files
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]squeeze\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] [\f[I]file\f[R]\&...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Compress and decompress files using gzip, brotli, or zstd.
Supports pipe mode (stdin/stdout), multi\-file batch processing, and
gzip\-compatible flags.
.PP
With no files, reads from stdin and writes to stdout (pipe mode).
Output format defaults to gzip unless \f[B]\(enbrotli\f[R] or
\f[B]\(enzstd\f[R] is given.
.PP
Decompression (\f[B]\-d\f[R]) auto\-detects the format from magic bytes
\(em the file extension is not required.
